% Scala Language Ontology - CNL Format
% Extends oo_ontology.cnl with Scala-specific concepts

% File/Module types
Every scala-compilation-unit is a compilation-unit.
Every scala-package is a namespace.

% Type definitions
Every scala-class is a class.
Every scala-trait is a trait.
Every scala-object is a class.
Every scala-enum is an enum.
Every scala-type-alias is a type-alias.
Every scala-case-class is a scala-class.

% Members
Every scala-method is a method.
Every scala-function is a function.
Every scala-field is a field.
Every scala-constructor is a constructor.

% Parameters
Every scala-parameter is a parameter.

% Import
Every scala-import is an import.

% Exception handling
Every scala-try-block is a try-block.
Every scala-catch-clause is a catch-clause.
Every scala-finally-clause is a finally-clause.
Every scala-throw-statement is a throw-statement.

% Control flow
Every scala-return-statement is a return-statement.

% Other
Every scala-variable is a variable.
Every scala-constant is a field.
Every scala-reference is a reference.
Every scala-annotation is an attribute.
Every scala-anonymous-function is an anonymous-function.

% Scala-Specific Concepts
Every sealed-trait is a trait.
Every abstract-class is a class.
Every case-object is a class.
Every package-object is a class.
Every implicit-class is a class.
Every value-class is a class.

% Access Modifiers
Every public-member is a member.
Every private-member is a member.
Every protected-member is a member.

% Code Smells
Every scala-god-class is a god-class.
Every scala-long-method is a long-method.
